title: Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.30 Frankfurt, Germany (Remaster)
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.30 Frankfurt, Germany   

Led Zeppelin  6-30-1980		
Frankfurt "Festhalle"  
Frankfurt, Germany
Bertha Remaster of the first generation cassette soundboard
Bertha Remasters are not DEFINITIVE. They are an ALTERNATIVE

Source: 
Excellent soundboard recording.

Details: 
The recording is a very good balanced professional board tape.

Tracklist:

101 - Train Kept A Rollin
102 - Nobody's Fault But Mine
103 - Black Dog
104 - In The Evening
105 - Rain Song
106 - Hot Dog
107 - All Of My Love
108 - Trampled underfoot
109 - Since I've Been Loving You
201 - Achilles Last Stand
202 - White Summer
203 - Kashmir
204 - Stairway to Heaven
205 - Rock and Roll
206 - Money
207 - Whole Lotta Love (incl. Let That Boy Boogie, Frankfurt Special)

Notes:
Digitally remastered using a custom built, Dual-DAW, nicknamed Bertha.  
Completed on January 15, 2005. The source is purported to be a 1st gen 
cassette off the master.

Comments: 
This show must be tied with the night before for the best 1980 show ever! 
What an excellent show. One of the few 1980 shows that has no moments of 
apathy or sluggishness. Fresh ideas and old ones are mixed and the result 
is one of the best concerts ever in Led Zeppelin's career. Achilles Last 
Stand is excellent and one of the strongest versions ever and the encores 
are simply amazing. Robert's voice is great ... he hits all the high notes. 
Jimmy tried calm down the audience while his playing in White Summer 
'cause he didn't hear himself! What makes this recording more interesting is 
presentation of Phil Carson, who joined the band for Money. He was 
introduced as "the man who used to play bass for Dusty Springfield"
